# GitHub client and cache

- Distinguish: not-found, rate-limited, unauthorized, server-error, network — never collapse all to 500
- Honor `Retry-After` and `X-RateLimit-Remaining` / `X-RateLimit-Reset`
- Fleet gate (`internal/ratelimit`) before upstream fetch; observe headers into Redis
- Cache key `gh:repo:{owner}/{name}`, TTL 5m; lock key `gh:lock:{owner}/{name}` via `SET NX` + expiry
- Concurrent cache miss → exactly one GitHub call; handle lock-holder death via lock TTL
- Sync/async refresh must invalidate the cache key
- Optional `GITHUB_TOKEN` via env only
